# Import Aliases

This project uses two path aliases for cleaner imports:

## `@framework/` - Framework & Infrastructure

Use for all framework/infrastructure code (design system, contexts, hooks, utilities):

```javascript
// Design system components
import { CTAButton, TextInputControl, Flex } from '@framework/components/ariane';

// Context
import { useAnnotations } from '@framework/context/AnnotationContext';

// Hooks
import { usePrototypes } from '@framework/hooks/usePrototypes';

// Core utilities
import { prototypeEntries } from '@framework/core/prototype-utils';
```

## `@/` - General Source

Use for general src directory references (prototypes, local assets):

```javascript
// Prototype imports (less common - prototypes are auto-discovered)
import MyComponent from '@/prototypes/my-prototype/components/MyComponent';
```

## Framework Directory Structure

The `src/_framework/` directory contains all updatable infrastructure:

```
src/_framework/
├── components/
│   ├── ariane/          # Design system (UI components)
│   ├── MainContent.jsx  # Prototype shell
│   └── PrototypeSelector.jsx
├── context/             # React contexts
├── hooks/               # Custom hooks
├── core/                # Core utilities
└── styles/              # Shared styles
```

## Why This Structure?

The `_framework` directory groups all infrastructure code that can be updated from the boilerplate without affecting your prototypes in `src/prototypes/`.
